Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Zest and halve @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, half the @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Swap in broccoli for potatoes. Roast until browned and tender, 15-20 minutes.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, juice from half the lemon, @celery salt{1/2%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1.5%tsp}. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and scallion greens; toss to coat. Season generously with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Place @butter{1%TBSP} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Slice @demi-baguettes{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through. Brush melted butter onto cut sides of bread. Place, cut sides up, directly on oven rack (or use a baking sheet); toast until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

While baguettes toast, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Toss in a second medium bowl with a large drizzle of olive oil, @smoked paprika{1/2%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, remaining @celery salt{1/2%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and scallion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} and lemon zest to taste.

Fill toasted baguettes with shrimp, as much slaw as you like, and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired.

Divide shrimp rolls and potato wedges between plates. Slice remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side.

> TIP: If you have ketchup on hand, serve some on the side for dipping.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.